verbose_text: The cholesterol efflux rate in the peritoneal macrophages and hepatocytes from the rabbits in the atherosclerosis group was significantly lower than that in the control group rabbits (peritoneal macrophages : 16.48 +/-4.10 vs. 24.93 +/-3.85%, P < 0.01; hepatocytes : 3.25 +/-0.97 vs. 5.29 +/-1.71%, P < 0.05), while the peritoneal macrophages and hepatocytes from the rabbits treated with rosiglitazone showed a significantly enhanced HDL induced cholesterol efflux as compared with the atherosclerosis group (peritoneal macrophages : 44.50 +/-6.19 vs. 16.48 +/-4.10%, P < 0.01; hepatocytes : 8.50 +/-1.18 vs. 3.25 +/-0.97%, P < 0.01; XREF_FIG).
